Thank you for your interest in Sacramento State!


This articulation agreement displays the lower-division courses required in the major: Sacramento State courses on the left and approved (articulated) transfer courses on the right. Although completion of the coursework listed below is not mandatory prior to admission, students are advised to complete as much lower-division course preparation as possible prior to transfer.


Additional Resources:

  • See the University Catalog for the full listing of degree requirements for this major.
  • Visit our Sac State Apply page for more information about our campus!
  • Visit the Admissions website for current transfer admission requirements.
  • Connect with an Admissions Counselor.

requirement.name: Courses approved for Second Semester Composition Graduation Requirement

templateAssets.content:
1. All required courses in the major, all electives in the major, ENGL 5 (or English 1A equivalent), and ENGL 20 (or an approved second semester composition course) must be completed with a grade of "C-" or better.
  2. Foreign Language Graduation Requirement Exemption: Students graduating with a B.S. in Mechanical Engineering will not be subject to the University's Foreign Language Graduation Requirement. Students who change major may be subject to the University's Foreign Language Graduation Requirement.
  3. Specific General Education (G.E.) exceptions may apply to Engineering majors. Please see our Mechanical Engineering GE Worksheet for additional details.
  4. Prior to transfer, it is strongly recommended that students complete all lower-division Mathematics, Science, and Engineering courses. In addition, students are also recommended to complete at least 18 units of G.E. coursework other than the Natural Sciences. Failure to do so may increase the time required for graduation.
  5. Students with catalog rights prior to Fall 2002 are required to complete PHYS 11B.
  6. For additional information, please visit: Department of Mechanical Engineering.
